The '''1978 Thessaloniki earthquake''' ({{lang-el|Μεγάλος Σεισμός της Θεσσαλονίκης}}) occurred on 20 June at {{Tooltip|23:03 local time|20:03 UTC}}. The shock registered 6.2 on the [[moment magnitude scale]], had a maximum [[Mercalli intensity scale|Mercalli intensity]] of VIII (''Severe''), and was felt throughout [[northern Greece]], [[Yugoslavia]] and [[Bulgaria]]. It was the largest event in the area since the [[1932 Ierissos earthquake]].<ref name="Maniateas">{{cite book |title= 100+1 Years of Greece |volume=Volume 2 |publisher= Maniateas Publishing |year= 1999 |location=Athens |pages=210–211}}</ref>

