{{Infobox television | show_name = Al-Qahera Al-Youm | image = Al-Qahira Al-Youm logo.jpg | caption = ''Al-Qahira Al-Youm'' logo | genre = [[News]] | creator = [[Orbit Communications Company]] | director = | developer = Mediagates | presenter = Gamal Enaiet, Mariam Zaki and others. | country = Egypt | language = Arabic | num_seasons = 16 | num_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | editor = | location = Madinat al entag el-elamy 6 October | runtime = 3 hours | network = Al Yawm available exclusively DTH on Alfa package on OSN and other distribution platforms | first_aired = 1999 | website = http://alfatv.com/ }}
'''Al Qahera Al Youm''' ({{lang-ar|القاهرة اليوم}}, English: ''Cairo Today'') is an [[Egypt|Egyptian]] live [[television]] [[talk show]] that broadcasts nearly throughout the year from the 6th of October studios located in [[Greater Cairo|Cairo]]. ''Al Qahera Al-Youm'' is one of the most popular and influential shows in the [[Middle East]] with millions of viewers world wide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/QAlYoum/|title=AlQahera AlYoum - القاهرة اليوم|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-14}}</ref> Hosted by Gamal Enaiet with Mariam Zaki and others. The program efficiently covers all aspects of life in [[Egypt]] from politics, to arts, sports, cultural and economic issues, and even international affairs. It airs on Al Yawm channel which is produced by Mediagates part of [[Orbit Communications Company]] now known as the [[OSN]]. The Show currently broadcasts throughout the week, from Sunday to Thursday.
