'''Benin Marina''' is a four-star hotel in [[Cotonou]], [[Benin]]. It is located at Boulevard De La Marina, B.P. 1901 in the Haie Vive neighborhood. It is the largest hotel in the country.<ref name="Butler">{{Cite book|last=Butler|first=Stuart|title=Benin|year=2006|publisher=[[Bradt Travel Guides]], The Globe Pequot Press|location=[[Guilford, Connecticut]]|page=92}}</ref> It is located in a large building which was formerly a [[Sheraton Hotels and Resorts|Sheraton]] hotel,<ref name="HamBainbridge2006">{{cite book|last1=Ham|first1=Anthony|last2=Bainbridge|first2=James|title=West Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JVdWavZlYKgC&pg=PA99|accessdate=9 March 2011|date=15 October 2006|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74059-771-5|page=99}}</ref>west of the old port of Cotonou.<ref name="KrausReid2010">{{cite book|last1=Kraus|first1=Erika|last2=Reid|first2=Felicie|title=Benin (Other Places Travel Guide)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=op5eAvnZfG0C&pg=PA58|accessdate=9 March 2011|date=26 January 2010|publisher=Other Places Publishing|isbn=978-0-9822619-1-0|page=58}}</ref> Set in landscaped gardens, the hotel contains two swimming pools, three tennis courts and small 9-hole golf course.<ref name="Butler"/>The building is only four storeys high but covers a significant area of land. The swimming pool is located next to the beach. The hotel has 200 rooms, 1 Royal Suite, 8 Junior Suites and 12 bungalows. The hotel contains the 'Le Popo' Coffeeshop Restaurant,  'Les Tanekas' Grill Bar by the pool,  'Le Nokoué' Pianobar and the 'Le Tèkè' Night Club / Karaoke Bar. The hotel is occasionally  used for important diplomatic meetings in Cotonou and contains 1 conference room and 6 meeting rooms.

