[[File:Schiedam windmolen Nolet.jpg|thumb|De Nolet]] '''''De Nolet''''' (also known as '''''Noletmolen''''') is a [[wind turbine]] in [[Schiedam]], [[Kingdom of the Netherlands|The Netherlands]] which is disguised as a traditional [[List of windmills in Schiedam|Schiedam windmill]]. ''De Nolet'' has a tower height of 43 metres and a gross height of 55 metres including its rotor tips.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.molens.nl/site/dbase/molen.php?mid=1322|title=Noletmolen |publisher=[[De Hollandsche Molen]]|author=|date=|website=molens.nl|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref><ref>http://www.molendatabase.nl/nederland/molen.php?nummer=1280 Database of Mills</ref>
It is 9 metres higher than ''[[De Noord]]'' which is the tallest [[windmill]] in the world.
''De Nolet'' was built in 2005 by the Nolet Distillery to power their brewing factory which produces the world-famous [[Ketel One]] vodkas and gins.
