{{bilateral|Djibouti–France|Djibouti|France}}

'''Djibouti–France relations''' refers to the [[bilateralism|current and historical relationship]] between [[Djibouti]] and [[France]]. Djibouti was obtained as a colony by France in 1862 and officially controlled Djibouti until it received independence in 1977. Djibouti maintains military and economic agreements with France which provide continued security and economic assistance. The largest [[Military of France|French military base]] in [[Africa]] is located in Djibouti's territorial waters in the [[Red Sea]].<ref>[http://www.cfr.org/publication/12578/french_military_in_africa.html French military in Africa] Council on Foreign Relations</ref>

