[[File:OnzeTaal2017.jpg|thumb|Onze Taal offices]] '''Genootschap Onze Taal''' (''Society for our language'') is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] society dedicated to the [[Dutch language]]. It was founded in 1931, initially to guard the language against what was seen as an invasion of [[Germanism (linguistics)|Germanisms]].<ref>[https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2004/08/02/zoiezo-7696166-a1209707 Zoiezo (''in Dutch'')], ''[[NRC Handelsblad]]''</ref>
The society publishes a journal, ''Onze Taal'', and a number of regularly appearing booklets on spelling, the most notable of which is the ''[[White Booklet]]''. It also has an advisory service, the ''Taaladviesdienst''.<ref>{{Cite book | last = Waardenburg | first = Marten | title = Zicht op Communicatie | publisher = Kluwer | date = 2004 | page = 377 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=3qWsbYtBNesC&pg=PA377 | isbn = 978-90-13-00680-3}}</ref>
