{{speciesbox | name = ''Tarentola raziana'' | image = | image_caption = | status = NT | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = | genus = Tarentola | species = raziana | authority = [[Hans Hermann Schleich|Schleich]] (1984) | synonyms = | synonyms_ref =<ref name="RDB"/> }} '''''Tarentola raziana''''' (English name: '''Razean''' or '''Raso wall gecko''') is a [[species]] of [[gecko]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Phyllodactylidae]]. The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands, they are founded in the island of [[Santa Luzia, Cape Verde|Santa Luzia]] and the islets of [[Ilhéu Branco|Branco]] and [[Ilhéu Raso|Raso]]<ref name="RDB">{{NRDB species|genus=Tarentola |species=raziana|accessdate=17 March 2017}}</ref> The species was named in by [[Hans Hermann Schleich]] in 1984.
==Etymology== The [[specific name (zoology)|specific name]] is named after the islet Raso where it is founded.<ref name="RDB"/>
==Taxonomy== The subspecies were elevated from ''Tarentola caboverdiana raziana'' by Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza en 2012.<ref>Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza, ''An integrative taxonomic revision of the Tarentola geckos (Squamata, Phyllodactylidae) of the Cape Verde Islands.'' Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 2012, vol. 164, no. 2, p. 328-360</ref>
